org.cornutum.tcases.conditions

Interface ICondition

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IAssertion, IConjunct, IDisjunct
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractAssertion, AllOf, AnyOf, Assert, AssertLess, AssertMore, AssertNot, AssertNotLess, AssertNotMore, Between, BoundedAssertion, ConditionSet, Conjunction, ContainsAll, ContainsAny, Disjunction, Equals, Not

    public interface ICondition
    A condition that evaluates a set of test case properties.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static ICondition ALWAYS
      A condition that is always satisfied by any PropertySet.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      Implements the Visitor pattern for this condition.

    • Field Detail

      • ALWAYS

        static final ICondition ALWAYS
        A condition that is always satisfied by any PropertySet.

    • Method Detail

      • satisfied

        boolean satisfied(PropertySet properties)
        Returns true if this condition is satisfied by the given test case properties.

      • compatible

        boolean compatible(PropertySet properties)
        Returns true if this condition is compatible with the given test case properties. A condition is "compatible" with these properties if it is already satisfied or if it could be satisfied with the addition of more properties.

      • accept

        void accept(IConditionVisitor visitor)
        Implements the Visitor pattern for this condition.
